  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Natural Capital Accounting and Valuation of Ecosystem Services (Brazil, China, India, Mexico, South Africa)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The EU, with the UN, will build on existing agreed methodology and develop new analyses, tools and operational approaches with a view to assessing the benefits that ecosystems and biodiversity can provide to the economy. As a result, it is expected to ensure and demonstrate that the output is used by policy makers in 5 partner countries to make better-informed decisions in relation to policies impacting biodiversity and the environment more broadly.</narrative>
  </description>
